&lt;p&gt;Are you currently a student nurse due to qualify in January/March 2021?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Nurses that clearly demonstrate and encompass our Trusts Values and Behaviours to enable us to make a difference. Join us at Tees, Esk and Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust as a Newly Qualified RMN/RNLD and together we can strive to deliver our ultimate goal in providing exceptional patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have Registered Nurse positions available across all our localities in a variety of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Band 5 - £24,907 to £30,615 per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Tees, Esk and Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust (TEWV), provide a range of mental health and learning disability services in Durham, Darlington, Tees, York and parts of North Yorkshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All interviews will take place via Microsoft Teams on Wednesday 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We will offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a guaranteed interview to students due to qualify in January/March 2021&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;full constructive feedback to everyone interviewed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;all successful applicants permanent positions with the Trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;supportive preceptorship arrangements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 -33 days annual leave with the option to purchase additional days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;flexible working opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;free car parking, cycle to work scheme and childcare vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;access to employee support, independent counselling, chaplaincy and physiotherapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;great career development opportunities staff discounts with many retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
